<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<task id="045" project="code-quality-and-assurance-r1">
  <metadata>
    <title>Final Update to testing-and-code-quality.md Procedure</title>
    <phase>5: Enforcement &amp; Documentation</phase>
    <status>completed</status>
    <estimated-hours>2</estimated-hours>
    <dependencies>041</dependencies>
    <blocks>090</blocks>
    <tags>documentation</tags>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    Perform a final comprehensive update to docs/procedures/testing-and-code-quality.md to ensure it
    reflects the complete quality system as fully implemented. Verify all new tools (added in task 041)
    are accurately described, cross-reference with the root CLAUDE.md to ensure AI agent instructions
    are consistent, and update any sections that reference the old state of the codebase (before this
    project). This is the final documentation polish pass — the document should be accurate and
    complete after this task.
  </prompt>

  <role>
    Technical writer specializing in developer procedure documentation with expertise in ensuring
    cross-document consistency across large codebases. Skilled at identifying gaps and inconsistencies
    between related documentation files.
  </role>

  <goal>
    A fully accurate and complete testing-and-code-quality.md that reflects the codebase's quality
    system post-project. All references to the old state (pre-project) are updated, all new tools are
    documented, and the document is consistent with the root CLAUDE.md and the new onboarding guide.
    This document becomes the authoritative reference for the quality system.
  </goal>

  <context>
    <background>
      Task 041 added new tool sections to testing-and-code-quality.md. This task is the final polish
      pass that ensures the document is cohesive, consistent, and complete:

      Consistency checks to perform:
      1. Cross-reference with root CLAUDE.md: the Commands section in CLAUDE.md lists build and test
         commands. Verify they match what is documented in testing-and-code-quality.md. If CLAUDE.md
         is outdated (does not include the new quality commands), note the discrepancy and optionally
         update CLAUDE.md's Commands table.
      2. Cross-reference with onboarding guide (task 042): the "Run Quality Checks Locally" section
         of the onboarding guide should list the same commands as testing-and-code-quality.md.
         Verify consistency.
      3. Outdated references: search for any references to the pre-project state — for example,
         mentions of "TODO: add linting" or references to only having dotnet test coverage without
         the new CI checks. Update these to reflect current state.
      4. Section completeness: verify the document covers the full quality lifecycle:
         - Pre-commit (Husky hooks)
         - Pre-push (if applicable)
         - PR quality gates (CI jobs, their names, what each checks)
         - Nightly quality (workflow, what it checks)
         - Weekly quality (summary job, what it aggregates)
         - Quarterly quality (reference to the runbook)
      5. ADR references: verify that ADRs cited in the document are referenced correctly and still
         exist in .claude/adr/ (no references to deleted or renumbered ADRs).

      This task is intentionally narrower than task 041 — task 041 added content, this task audits
      and polishes the complete document for accuracy and consistency.
    </background>
    <relevant-files>
      <file>docs/procedures/testing-and-code-quality.md (modify — final accuracy and consistency pass)</file>
      <file>CLAUDE.md (read — verify command consistency)</file>
      <file>docs/guides/code-quality-onboarding.md (read — verify command consistency with task 042 output)</file>
    </relevant-files>
  </context>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="spec">Any changes to CLAUDE.md must be conservative and additive. Do not restructure CLAUDE.md — only update the Commands table if commands are genuinely missing or incorrect. CLAUDE.md is used by all AI sessions and any errors have wide impact.</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec">Do not re-document content that is already accurate in task 041's additions. This is a consistency and completeness audit, not a rewrite. Changes should be targeted corrections, not wholesale rewrites of task 041 content.</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec">If inconsistencies are found between testing-and-code-quality.md and the onboarding guide, resolve them in testing-and-code-quality.md (authoritative source) and note the discrepancy for the onboarding guide author to address.</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec">Document any intentional gaps (things not yet implemented or not yet documented) with a clear "Future: ..." note rather than leaving implicit gaps that suggest the document is complete when it is not.</constraint>
  </constraints>

  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>docs/procedures/testing-and-code-quality.md</file>
      <file>CLAUDE.md</file>
      <file>docs/guides/code-quality-onboarding.md</file>
    </files>
  </knowledge>

  <steps>
    <step order="1">Read docs/procedures/testing-and-code-quality.md in full (including task 041's additions) to understand the current complete state of the document.</step>
    <step order="2">Read the Commands section of root CLAUDE.md to identify any quality-related commands that are listed there but not in testing-and-code-quality.md, or vice versa. Document discrepancies.</step>
    <step order="3">Read docs/guides/code-quality-onboarding.md (task 042 output) to verify its "Run Locally" commands match testing-and-code-quality.md. Document any discrepancies.</step>
    <step order="4">Perform an outdated-reference audit of testing-and-code-quality.md: search for phrases like "TODO", "will be", "planned", "not yet implemented" that refer to things now implemented in this project. Update these to describe the current implemented state.</step>
    <step order="5">Verify section coverage of the quality lifecycle: confirm the document has explicit sections for pre-commit, PR gates, nightly, weekly, and quarterly quality. If any lifecycle stage is missing, add a brief section or reference.</step>
    <step order="6">Verify ADR references: for each ADR cited in testing-and-code-quality.md, confirm the ADR file exists in .claude/adr/ with the correct number. Fix any references to non-existent or renumbered ADRs.</step>
    <step order="7">If CLAUDE.md's Commands table is missing quality commands (e.g., `prettier --check` or `npx eslint`), add them to CLAUDE.md's Commands table with appropriate descriptions. Keep additions minimal and consistent with the existing table format.</step>
    <step order="8">Make all identified corrections to testing-and-code-quality.md. Group related changes and verify the document reads cohesively after all updates.</step>
    <step order="9">Create a brief audit note at projects/code-quality-and-assurance-r1/notes/documentation-audit.md listing: inconsistencies found, corrections made, and any intentional gaps documented with "Future:" notes.</step>
    <step order="10">Update TASK-INDEX.md: change task 045 status from pending to completed.</step>
  </steps>

  <outputs>
    <output type="file">docs/procedures/testing-and-code-quality.md (final accuracy and consistency pass)</output>
    <output type="file">CLAUDE.md (minimal updates to Commands table if needed)</output>
    <output type="report">projects/code-quality-and-assurance-r1/notes/documentation-audit.md</output>
  </outputs>

  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion>testing-and-code-quality.md has no outdated references to pre-project state (no "TODO: add" or "will be implemented" for things now implemented)</criterion>
    <criterion>testing-and-code-quality.md covers all quality lifecycle stages: pre-commit, PR gates, nightly, weekly, quarterly</criterion>
    <criterion>All ADR references in testing-and-code-quality.md point to files that exist in .claude/adr/</criterion>
    <criterion>Quality commands in testing-and-code-quality.md are consistent with CLAUDE.md's Commands table</criterion>
    <criterion>documentation-audit.md exists listing inconsistencies found and corrections made</criterion>
    <criterion>Any changes to CLAUDE.md are limited to the Commands table and are additive</criterion>
    <criterion>TASK-INDEX.md updated to reflect task completion</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>
</task>
